 </p>
 <p class="bb_paragraph">
  From the illustrators behind the comedy horror webtoon
  <i>
   Erma
  </i>
  ,
  <i>
   Erma: The Game
  </i>
  is a point-and-click adventure game, where you play as the titular character Erma. As your science fair project goes explosively awry, you must find the pieces that have scattered throughout your hometown and gather them to rebuild your project.
 </p>
 <p class="bb_paragraph">
 </p>
 <p class="bb_paragraph">
  Along the way, you'll come across the wayward townsfolk who have found the pieces of your project before you. Barter with, trade for, and trap them with whatever you can find to get those pieces back. One man's trash is another's treasure, after all!
 </p>
 <p class="bb_paragraph">
 </p>
 <p class="bb_paragraph">
  Oh, and take care to search everything thoroughly. An old town like this can hide many secrets.
 </p>
 <p class="bb_paragraph">
 </p>
 <p class="bb_paragraph">
  By any chance, you wouldn't have happened to hear that whispering, did you?
 </p>
 <p class="bb_paragraph">
 </p>
 <h2 class="bb_tag" style="text-align: center">
  <span class="bb_img_ctn">
   <img alt="About" class="bb_img" height="79" src="https://shared.fastly.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/4150180/extras/915421598b0fa098a9abf56b0b591c22.avif" width="246"/>
  </span>
 </h2>
 <p class="bb_paragraph">
 </p>
 <p class="bb_paragraph">
  Inspired by
  <i>
   Pajama Sam
  </i>
  ,
  <i>
   Erma: The Game
  </i>
  is a point-and-click adventure and collection game. A simple inventory interface allows you to collect and combine various bits and baubles while you wander the areas around your small town.
 </p>
 <p class="bb_paragraph">
 </p>
 <p class="bb_paragraph">
  Pieces of your science fair project have been scattered across the map of your hometown, and each piece has been found by a different inhabitant. Figure out what they're looking for and use items found as you explore, investigate, and play minigames to satisfy the locals. Beat games, collect items, and figure out how to combine or use them to progress.
 </p>
 <p class="bb_paragraph">
 </p>
 <p class="bb_paragraph">
  Erma is a love-letter to horror. As such, the world has been filled with many fun little nods to a multitude of media. There's no rush; take your time to thoroughly explore the world and enjoy the animated detail drawn by the illustrators of Erma!
 </p>
